"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-08-08-olympic-swimmers-seine-bacteria-coca-cola\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Some Olympic swimmers are turning to drinking cola as a surprising part of their workout regimen.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 97, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheSeine River, the site of a number of athletic events at the Paris Games, has raised water quality-related concerns - namely, E.coli and fecal matter - for months, despite the fact that the French city spent $1.5 billion to de-pollute it.\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 291, \"end\": 297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9716672003439172, \"rank\": 0.024493017294039014, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The marathon swim test, meant to allow Olympians to preview the marathon swimming course, was canceled on Tuesday by the World Aquatics,per the Associated Press.\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 484, \"end\": 500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9957553191924826, \"rank\": 0.004262774922210548, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To mitigate the risk of bacterial infection, some athletes have taken to drinking Coca-Cola after swimming in the river.\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 585, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.9999738328562535, \"rank\": 2.6167827657065586e-05, \"text\": \"Coca-Cola\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no harm in drinking a Coke after a race,\\\" New Zealand triathlete\\u00a0Ainsley Thorptold The Wall Street Journal.\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you Google it, it says it can help.\\\"\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We will often have a Coca-Cola afterward just to try to flush out anything inside of us,\\\" Australian swimmer\\u00a0Moesha Johnson\\u00a0said.\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 805, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.9999738328562535, \"rank\": 2.6167827657065586e-05, \"text\": \"Coca-Cola\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}, {\"begin\": 874, \"end\": 884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.6375276915533055, \"rank\": 0.4835665378426631, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moesha\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Moesha\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moesha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moesha\"}, {\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"score\": 0.9999777713561755, \"rank\": 1.2473086928552724e-05, \"text\": \"Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lyndon_B._Johnson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just do what I am told by the professionals around me.\\\"\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Dr. Maria Abreu, president of the American Gastroenterological Association, was somewhat skeptical about the cleansing powers of the popular beverage brand.\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 987, \"end\": 992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"score\": 0.999567521068819, \"rank\": 0.0003062704073452412, \"text\": \"Maria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Maria\"}, {\"begin\": 993, \"end\": 998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Abreu\", \"score\": 0.616718731220608, \"rank\": 0.6214845194744689, \"text\": \"Abreu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Abreu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Abreu\"}, {\"begin\": 1017, \"end\": 1057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Gastroenterological_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"American Gastroenterological Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Gastroenterological_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Gastroenterological_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given that a healthy gut is more acidic than Coke, Abreu said, it's unlikely that the soda would be able to eliminate any unwanted bacteria.\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1191, \"end\": 1196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Abreu\", \"score\": 0.616718731220608, \"rank\": 0.6214845194744689, \"text\": \"Abreu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Abreu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bobby_Abreu\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These are young, athletic people,\\\" the doctor shared,according to PEOPLE.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are going to be healthy people whose stomach acid is going to be nice and robust.\\\"\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While Coke's bacteria-ridding capabilities are still more or less up for debate, the soda can be useful for a post-competition sugar rush.\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My coach advised me to [drink Coca-Cola] to restore those glycogen levels immediately,\\\" American swimmer Katie Grimes shared.\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1615, \"end\": 1624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.9999738328562535, \"rank\": 2.6167827657065586e-05, \"text\": \"Coca-Cola\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}, {\"begin\": 1673, \"end\": 1681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999880649285, \"rank\": 8.262507724865758e-09, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1690, \"end\": 1702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Grimes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Grimes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Grimes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Grimes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2026 Salon.com, LLC.\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1731, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salon.com\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salon.com\"}, {\"begin\": 1742, \"end\": 1745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999976416157167, \"rank\"